'I'm still hoping that it's going to get resolved. That's all."

The Department of Foreign Affairs told Daily Mail Australia in a statement: 'Where there have been concerns expressed about his [Mr Shilov's] health or welfare in prison, the Department has made representations to Russian authorities.

'Consular officials are also in regular communication with the man's family and his legal advisers about his case.'

